for me (Lenovo D330) the fix did work (you need to log off/ log on to restart mutter). If anybody else is affected by this on Ubuntu 19.04, here are the patched mutter packages I use:

[mutter_touchfix_debs.zip](/uploads/47d79d1bb80767c85a3f2e2533cfcd2b/mutter_touchfix_debs.zip)

where I just applied the one-liner on top of 3.32.1.

Here's the crash fix patch.

```
diff -u -r gtk+-3.24.3/modules/input/imquartz.c gtk+-3.24.3-working/modules/input/imquartz.c
--- gtk+-3.24.3/modules/input/imquartz.c        2019-01-13 19:06:51.000000000 -0800
+++ gtk+-3.24.3-working/modules/input/imquartz.c        2019-01-16 17:54:36.000000000 -0800
@@ -196,7 +196,7 @@
     {
       if (event->hardware_keycode == 0 && event->keyval == 0xffffff)
         /* update text input changes by mouse events */
-        return output_result (context, win);
+        return output_result (context, event->window);
       else
         return gtk_im_context_filter_keypress (qc->slave, event);
     }
```

`win` is NULL in this case. It seems ok to get GdkWindow from passed in GdkEvent in this case.

